        {
            "_id": "sSAVmevencpx75UB",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
            "name": "Pestilential Aura",
            "sort": 1100000,
            "system": {
                "actionCategory": {
                    "value": "defensive"
                },
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>5 feet, @Check[type:fortitude|dc:33]</p>\n<p>Creatures beginning their turn in the area while the vrykolakas is in its true form are exposed to bubonic plague.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Bubonic Plague</strong></p>\n<p>This widespread illness can sweep through entire communities, leaving few unaffected. The first indication of the disease is a telltale swelling of glands. In some cases, the disease can move into your lungs (pneumonic plague) or blood (septicemic plague), which is even more fatal.</p>\n<p>If you have bubonic plague, you can't remove the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Fatigued]{Fatigued} condition while affected.</p>\n<p><strong>Onset</strong> 1 day</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> fatigued (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Enfeebled]{Enfeebled 2} and fatigued (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Enfeebled]{Enfeebled 3}, fatigued, and take @Localize[PF2E.PersistentDamage.Bleed1d6.success] every [[/r 1d20 #minutes]]{1d20 minutes}</p>"
                },
